1 AN ACT relating to crime victim notification and making an appropriation therefor.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 27A IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) The Administrative Office of the Courts shall establish and maintain a crime
6 victim notification system.
7 (2) The system shall:
8 (a) Interface with any case management system operated by a county or
9 Commonwealth's attorney and the Department of Corrections to ensure the
10 prompt reporting and receiving of case information;
11 (b) Establish technical and operational protocols for system interoperability;
12 (c) Allow a victim, as defined in KRS 421.500, to register to receive
13 notifications regarding court proceedings, case dispositions, offender
14 custody status, and parole hearings and decisions related to the case for
15 which the victim has registered by providing requisite information
16 determined by the Administrative Office of the Courts;
17 (d) Allow a victim who elects to register for notifications to select multiple
18 methods of notification, including by telephone, email, and mobile
19 applications;
20 (e) Ensure confidentiality and secure handling of victim information in
21 compliance with applicable state and federal privacy requirements;
22 (f) Be available in multiple languages; and
23 (g) Permit a victim to opt out at any time and to have his or her personal
24 information deleted from the system.
25 (3) Nothing in this section shall limit the duties of public officers and agencies
26 required under KRS 421.500 to 421.575.
27 (4) If the crime victim notification system cannot be developed internally, the
